(265, 52, 6, '04 - Normal', 'Water pressure low', 'David discovered that it is not the washing machine pipe, but for some reason, the rain water tap in the courtyard only, is running with very little pressure.   There is no problem inside the house which makes it even more mysterious.   In addition, David said the Municipal switch is not functioning either, so even when the lever is pushed over to Municipal, it is the rain water that is trickling out only.   David said it would need Jackson to sort out.     What I don`t understand is why the pressure in the courtyard tap alone has altered when it had been working normally before.   In a nutshell, it appears that the problem is between the rain water tank motor and the courtyard taps.   Could it be the switch malfunctioning suddenly?', 293, 'Plumber', 'Other', 24, '2020-12-10 06:42:14', '2020-12-10 04:42:21', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0.00', '2020-12-10', '00:00:00', '0000-00-00', '00:00:00', '0000-00-00', '0.00', 0, 24, '2020-12-10 06:42:21'),
